1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:02,987
Five expensive, interlocking failures.

2
00:00:02,987 --> 00:00:08,987
One — ninety percent of clinical trials fail, costing two billion dollars per program.

3
00:00:08,987 --> 00:00:13,637
Two — biomedical tools generate association data, not causation.

4
00:00:13,637 --> 00:00:19,750
Three — the FDA now demands mechanistic causal evidence; most platforms cannot deliver it.

5
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:25,437
Four — omics workflows still require trained bioinformaticians, throttling adoption.

6
00:00:25,437 --> 00:00:33,562
Five — discovery pipelines are fragmented across vendors, with no auditable chain from raw sequencing to FDA submission.

